translated: Ehinger, Karl Gustav Johannes, regimental doctor, Halmstad, born March 7th, 1901 in Dalarö, Stockholm 1st parish, son of chief physician Johannes E. and Hilma Norberg. Married in 1932 to Birgit Eriksdotter Leksell. Children: Malin born in 1936, Berndt in 1937, and AU in 1946. Studied in Linköping in 1919, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine in Uppsala in 1925, became a medical licensed practitioner in Stockholm in 1932. Was an adjunct assistant at the Department of Pathology in Uppsala in 1926, medical doctor at Källvik's spring in the summer of 1928, medical doctor and temporary assistant at Stockholm Hospital in 1930, assistant physician at the medical department of Linköping Hospital in 1930-31 and 1932-33, temporary second deputy physician there from 1933-34, and temporary assistant physician and temporary deputy physician at Serafim la's medical polyclinic in 1934, as well as the same positions at the medical clinic from 1934-35, temporary deputy physician at Falun Hospital's medical department in 1935, second deputy physician at Serafimla's medical polyclinic from 1935-36, temporary battalion physician in the Boden Garrison from 1936-38, battalion physician in the staff of the Upper Norrland troops in 1938, battalion physician in the Gotha Artillery Regiment from 1939-41, and regimental doctor in the Halland Regiment since 1941. Interests include ornithology and philately.
